              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Safety Design Principles -->
            <div class="mb-8">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Mechatronic Safety Design</h2>
              
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">How Engineers Design Safety Into Systems:</h3>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">üõ°Ô∏è Fail-Safe Design</h4>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ If system breaks, it fails in the safest way possible</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Traffic lights default to flashing red if malfunction</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Elevator brakes engage if power fails</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Nuclear reactors shut down automatically if problems occur</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">üîÑ Redundancy</h4>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Multiple backup systems in case one fails</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Airplanes have multiple navigation systems</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Hospitals have backup power generators</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Cars have multiple braking systems (ABS + manual)</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
